oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Shellmound Depot
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Shellmound Depot near Chattanooga. Several people, including Dr. Moss, are standing outside the depot. A man can be seen inside the ticketing booth of the depot. In the adjacent garden area, a man is watering elephant ear leaves.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Railroad stations; Plants
